# Testing Rules

## Backend -- Unit Tests (.NET)

- Framework: xUnit + Moq + Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.InMemory
- Naming: `MethodName_Scenario_ShouldExpectedResult`
  - `CreateAsync_WhenUsernameExists_ShouldReturnFailure`
  - `Login_WithInvalidPassword_ShouldReturnUnauthorized`
- Pattern: Arrange-Act-Assert
- One test class per service: `MusicServiceTests.cs`, `ListServiceTests.cs`
- Mock external dependencies with Moq (`Mock<ILogger<T>>`, `Mock<ICoreFileService>`)
- Use InMemoryDatabase with unique DB name per test to avoid cross-test pollution

```csharp
var options = new DbContextOptionsBuilder<AppDbContext>()
    .UseInMemoryDatabase(databaseName: Guid.NewGuid().ToString())
    .Options;
using var context = new AppDbContext(options);
```

## Backend -- Integration Tests (.NET)

- Use `WebApplicationFactory<Program>` for full HTTP pipeline tests
- Test real request/response through controllers, middleware, and services
- Use InMemory DB or test PostgreSQL via Docker (`docker-compose.test.yml`)
- Verify status codes, response body, and side effects

```csharp
public class FilesControllerIntegrationTests : IClassFixture<WebApplicationFactory<Program>>
{
    private readonly HttpClient _client;

    public FilesControllerIntegrationTests(WebApplicationFactory<Program> factory)
    {
        _client = factory.WithWebHostBuilder(builder =>
        {
            builder.ConfigureServices(services =>
            {
                // Replace DB with InMemory for tests
            });
        }).CreateClient();
    }
}
```

## Frontend (TypeScript)

- Framework: Vitest + React Testing Library (required, not optional)
- Config: `vitest.config.ts` at `frontend/` root
- Naming: `describe('Component')` -> `it('should display list when data loads')`
- Test user interactions, not implementation details
- Test loading, success, and error states
- Test form validation with invalid inputs
- Test permission-gated UI elements (`hasPermission` mocking)

React Query test wrapper:
```tsx
function createTestWrapper() {
  const queryClient = new QueryClient({
    defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } },
  })
  return ({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) => (
    <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>{children}</QueryClientProvider>
  )
}
```

## Coverage Expectations

- Service methods: every public method must have at least one happy-path and one error-path test
- Controllers: integration tests for all POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints
- Frontend hooks: test query success, error, and loading states
- Target: 80%+ line coverage on services

## Test Health

- All existing tests MUST compile and pass -- broken tests are treated as violations
- Tests must stay in sync with production code (updated constructors, removed models, etc.)
- Run `dotnet test` and `npm test` in CI before merge

## General

- No `console.log` left in production code
- No skipped/ignored tests without a tracking issue
- Test data should be self-contained -- never depend on external state or ordering
